{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# SPARQL Tools for Agentic Systems\n",
    "> Tools for agents to construct, validate, and execute SPARQL queries with ontological guidance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#| default_exp tools.sparql"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#| export\n",
    "from __future__ import annotations\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import json\n",
    "import re\n",
    "from typing import Dict, List, Any, Optional, Union, Tuple, Callable, Set\n",
    "from rdflib import Graph, RDF, URIRef, Literal, Namespace, Dataset\n",
    "from rdflib.plugins.sparql import prepareQuery, algebra\n",
    "from rdflib.plugins.sparql.parser import parseQuery\n",
    "from rdflib.plugins.sparql.algebra import translateQuery\n",
    "\n",
    "from cogitarelink.core.debug import get_logger\n",
    "from cogitarelink.cli.cli import Agent, ToolRegistry\n",
    "from cogitarelink.reason.sandbox import reason_over"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#| exporti\n",
    "__all__ = ['SPARQLToolAgent', 'sparql_parser_tools', 'sparql_validator_tools', 'sparql_execution_tools']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# SPARQL Tools Architecture\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook, we'll create a suite of tools for working with SPARQL queries in agentic systems. These tools enable agents to:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Parse and analyze SPARQL queries** - Extract query components and validate syntax\n",
    "2. **Validate queries against ontologies** - Check domain/range constraints and detect inconsistencies\n",
    "3. **Execute queries across endpoints** - Run queries against local or remote SPARQL endpoints\n",
    "4. **Refine queries with LLM guidance** - Iteratively improve queries based on feedback\n",
    "\n",
    "The architecture follows the modular design principles of CogitareLink, with clean separation of concerns:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "┌─────────────────────────┐      ┌──────────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────────┐\n",
    "│   SPARQL Parser Tools   │─────▶│ SPARQL Validator Tools│─────▶│SPARQL Execution Tools│\n",
    "└─────────────────────────┘      └──────────────────────┘      └─────────────────────┘\n",
    "          ▲                                 ▲                             ▲\n",
    "          │                                 │                             │\n",
    "          │                                 │                             │\n",
    "          │                                 │                             │\n",
    "          └─────────────────┬──────────────┴─────────────────────────────┘\n",
    "                            │\n",
    "                  ┌───────────────────┐\n",
    "                  │  Agent Interface  │\n",
    "                  └───────────────────┘\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "This architecture provides several advantages for agentic systems:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Decoupled components** - Modules can be used independently or together\n",
    "2. **Progressive validation** - Queries can be checked before execution\n",
    "3. **Structured feedback** - Validation errors produce actionable insights for LLMs\n",
    "4. **Extensible design** - New functionality can be added without modifying existing code"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 1. SPARQL Parser Tools\n",
    "\n",
    "First, let's create tools for robustly parsing SPARQL queries using RDFLib."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#| export\n",
    "log = get_logger(\"sparql-tools\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#| export\n",
    "def sparql_parser_tools() -> Dict[str, Callable]:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Create a set of tools for parsing and analyzing SPARQL queries.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        Dict mapping tool names to tool functions\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    tools = {}\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def parse_sparql_query(query: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Parse a SPARQL query using RDFLib and extract its components.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Parameters:\n",
    "            query: SPARQL query string\n",
    "            \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            Dictionary with parsed query components\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            # Parse the query using RDFLib\n",
    "            parsed_query = parseQuery(query)\n",
    "            algebra_tree = translateQuery(parsed_query)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Extract query type (SELECT, CONSTRUCT, etc)\n",
    "            query_type = algebra_tree.name\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Extract prefixes\n",
    "            prefix_pattern = re.compile(r'PREFIX\\s+(\\w+):\\s*<([^>]+)>', re.IGNORECASE)\n",
    "            prefixes = {prefix: uri for prefix, uri in prefix_pattern.findall(query)}\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Extract query variables\n",
    "            variables = []\n",
    "            if hasattr(algebra_tree, 'PV'):\n",
    "                variables = [str(v) for v in algebra_tree.PV]\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Extract basic graph patterns\n",
    "            bgps = extract_basic_graph_patterns(algebra_tree)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": True,\n",
    "                \"query_type\": query_type,\n",
    "                \"prefixes\": prefixes,\n",
    "                \"variables\": variables,\n",
    "                \"bgps\": bgps,\n",
    "                \"algebra\": str(algebra_tree)\n",
    "            }\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            log.error(f\"Failed to parse SPARQL query: {str(e)}\")\n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": False,\n",
    "                \"error\": f\"Failed to parse SPARQL query: {str(e)}\",\n",
    "                \"query\": query\n",
    "            }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def extract_basic_graph_patterns(algebra_tree) -> List[Dict[str, str]]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Recursively extract basic graph patterns from a SPARQL algebra tree.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Parameters:\n",
    "            algebra_tree: SPARQL algebra tree from RDFLib\n",
    "            \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            List of triples as dictionaries\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        bgps = []\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Handle different algebra structures\n",
    "        if hasattr(algebra_tree, 'p') and algebra_tree.p.__class__.__name__ == 'BGP':\n",
    "            # Direct BGP access\n",
    "            for triple in algebra_tree.p.triples:\n",
    "                bgps.append({\n",
    "                    \"subject\": str(triple[0]),\n",
    "                    \"predicate\": str(triple[1]),\n",
    "                    \"object\": str(triple[2])\n",
    "                })\n",
    "        elif hasattr(algebra_tree, 'p'):\n",
    "            # Recursive case for nested patterns\n",
    "            bgps.extend(extract_basic_graph_patterns(algebra_tree.p))\n",
    "        elif hasattr(algebra_tree, 'p1') and hasattr(algebra_tree, 'p2'):\n",
    "            # Handle binary operators like UNION, JOIN\n",
    "            bgps.extend(extract_basic_graph_patterns(algebra_tree.p1))\n",
    "            bgps.extend(extract_basic_graph_patterns(algebra_tree.p2))\n",
    "        elif algebra_tree.__class__.__name__ == 'BGP':\n",
    "            # Direct BGP\n",
    "            for triple in algebra_tree.triples:\n",
    "                bgps.append({\n",
    "                    \"subject\": str(triple[0]),\n",
    "                    \"predicate\": str(triple[1]),\n",
    "                    \"object\": str(triple[2])\n",
    "                })\n",
    "                \n",
    "        return bgps\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def build_graph_from_query(query: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Convert a SPARQL query's patterns to an RDF graph for validation.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Parameters:\n",
    "            query: SPARQL query string\n",
    "            \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            Dictionary with RDF graph in various formats\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            # Parse the query first\n",
    "            parse_result = parse_sparql_query(query)\n",
    "            if not parse_result.get(\"success\", False):\n",
    "                return parse_result\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Get BGPs and prefixes\n",
    "            bgps = parse_result.get(\"bgps\", [])\n",
    "            prefixes = parse_result.get(\"prefixes\", {})\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Create a graph from the BGPs\n",
    "            g = Graph()\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Add standard prefixes for common vocabularies\n",
    "            g.bind(\"rdf\", \"http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\")\n",
    "            g.bind(\"rdfs\", \"http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#\")\n",
    "            g.bind(\"owl\", \"http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#\")\n",
    "            g.bind(\"xsd\", \"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#\")\n",
    "            g.bind(\"schema\", \"https://schema.org/\")\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Add user-defined prefixes\n",
    "            for prefix, uri in prefixes.items():\n",
    "                g.bind(prefix, uri)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Define a special namespace for query variables\n",
    "            VAR_NS = Namespace(\"http://example.org/var/\")\n",
    "            g.bind(\"var\", VAR_NS)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Convert strings to RDFLib terms\n",
    "            for triple in bgps:\n",
    "                # Parse subject\n",
    "                if triple[\"subject\"].startswith(\"?\"):\n",
    "                    s = VAR_NS[triple[\"subject\"][1:]]\n",
    "                    # Mark as a variable\n",
    "                    g.add((s, RDF.type, VAR_NS[\"Variable\"]))\n",
    "                else:\n",
    "                    s = parse_term(triple[\"subject\"], prefixes)\n",
    "                    \n",
    "                # Parse predicate (almost always a URI)\n",
    "                p = parse_term(triple[\"predicate\"], prefixes)\n",
    "                \n",
    "                # Parse object\n",
    "                if triple[\"object\"].startswith(\"?\"):\n",
    "                    o = VAR_NS[triple[\"object\"][1:]]\n",
    "                    # Mark as a variable\n",
    "                    g.add((o, RDF.type, VAR_NS[\"Variable\"]))\n",
    "                else:\n",
    "                    o = parse_term(triple[\"object\"], prefixes)\n",
    "                \n",
    "                # Add the triple to the graph\n",
    "                g.add((s, p, o))\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Return the graph in multiple serialization formats\n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": True,\n",
    "                \"jsonld\": json.loads(g.serialize(format=\"json-ld\")),\n",
    "                \"turtle\": g.serialize(format=\"turtle\"),\n",
    "                \"triples_count\": len(g),\n",
    "                \"query\": query\n",
    "            }\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            log.error(f\"Failed to build graph from query: {str(e)}\")\n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": False,\n",
    "                \"error\": f\"Failed to build graph from query: {str(e)}\",\n",
    "                \"query\": query\n",
    "            }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def parse_term(term_str: str, prefixes: Dict[str, str]) -> Union[URIRef, Literal]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Parse a string term into RDFLib term.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Parameters:\n",
    "            term_str: String representation of a term\n",
    "            prefixes: Dictionary of prefixes to URIs\n",
    "            \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            RDFLib term (URIRef or Literal)\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        # URI in brackets\n",
    "        if term_str.startswith(\"<\") and term_str.endswith(\">\"):\n",
    "            return URIRef(term_str[1:-1])\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # String literal\n",
    "        if (term_str.startswith(\"\\'\") and term_str.endswith(\"\\'\")) or \\\n",
    "           (term_str.startswith('\"') and term_str.endswith('\"')):\n",
    "            return Literal(term_str[1:-1])\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Prefixed name\n",
    "        if \":\" in term_str:\n",
    "            prefix, local = term_str.split(\":\", 1)\n",
    "            if prefix in prefixes:\n",
    "                return URIRef(prefixes[prefix] + local)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Default to literal if we can't parse it\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            # Try numeric literal\n",
    "            if term_str.isdigit():\n",
    "                return Literal(int(term_str))\n",
    "            if all(c.isdigit() or c == '.' for c in term_str):\n",
    "                return Literal(float(term_str))\n",
    "        except:\n",
    "            pass\n",
    "            \n",
    "        # Fall back to string literal\n",
    "        return Literal(term_str)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def generate_sparql_summary(query: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Generate a human-readable summary of a SPARQL query.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Parameters:\n",
    "            query: SPARQL query string\n",
    "            \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            Dictionary with query summary\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            # Parse the query first\n",
    "            parse_result = parse_sparql_query(query)\n",
    "            if not parse_result.get(\"success\", False):\n",
    "                return parse_result\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Extract key components\n",
    "            query_type = parse_result.get(\"query_type\", \"\")\n",
    "            variables = parse_result.get(\"variables\", [])\n",
    "            bgps = parse_result.get(\"bgps\", [])\n",
    "            prefixes = parse_result.get(\"prefixes\", {})\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Get unique subjects and objects for entity summary\n",
    "            entities = set()\n",
    "            predicates = set()\n",
    "            for triple in bgps:\n",
    "                if not triple[\"subject\"].startswith(\"?\"):\n",
    "                    entities.add(triple[\"subject\"])\n",
    "                if not triple[\"object\"].startswith(\"?\"):\n",
    "                    entities.add(triple[\"object\"])\n",
    "                predicates.add(triple[\"predicate\"])\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Generate a natural language summary\n",
    "            nl_summary = f\"This {query_type} query \"\n",
    "            \n",
    "            if query_type in [\"SelectQuery\", \"Select\"]:\n",
    "                var_str = \", \".join([v.replace(\"?\", \"\") for v in variables])\n",
    "                nl_summary += f\"retrieves {var_str} \"\n",
    "            elif query_type in [\"ConstructQuery\", \"Construct\"]:\n",
    "                nl_summary += \"constructs new triples \"\n",
    "            elif query_type in [\"AskQuery\", \"Ask\"]:\n",
    "                nl_summary += \"checks if a pattern exists \"\n",
    "            \n",
    "            nl_summary += f\"with {len(bgps)} triple patterns using {len(predicates)} distinct predicates.\"\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Return the summary\n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": True,\n",
    "                \"query_type\": query_type,\n",
    "                \"variables_count\": len(variables),\n",
    "                \"variables\": variables,\n",
    "                \"triples_count\": len(bgps),\n",
    "                \"entities_count\": len(entities),\n",
    "                \"predicates_count\": len(predicates),\n",
    "                \"predicates\": list(predicates),\n",
    "                \"summary\": nl_summary,\n",
    "                \"query\": query\n",
    "            }\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            log.error(f\"Failed to summarize SPARQL query: {str(e)}\")\n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": False,\n",
    "                \"error\": f\"Failed to summarize SPARQL query: {str(e)}\",\n",
    "                \"query\": query\n",
    "            }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Add tools to the dictionary\n",
    "    tools[\"parse_sparql_query\"] = parse_sparql_query\n",
    "    tools[\"build_graph_from_query\"] = build_graph_from_query\n",
    "    tools[\"generate_sparql_summary\"] = generate_sparql_summary\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return tools"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 2. SPARQL Validator Tools\n",
    "\n",
    "Now, let's create tools for validating SPARQL queries against ontologies using our OBQC system."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#| export\n",
    "def sparql_validator_tools() -> Dict[str, Callable]:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Create a set of tools for validating SPARQL queries against ontologies.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        Dict mapping tool names to tool functions\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    tools = {}\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def validate_query_against_ontology(query: str, ontology_ttl: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Validate a SPARQL query against an ontology using OBQC rules.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Parameters:\n",
    "            query: SPARQL query string\n",
    "            ontology_ttl: Turtle representation of the ontology\n",
    "            \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            Dictionary with validation results\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            from cogitarelink.reason.obqc import check_query\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Get the validation summary\n",
    "            summary = check_query(query, ontology_ttl)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Parse results into a more structured format\n",
    "            violations = []\n",
    "            if summary:\n",
    "                for line in summary.strip().split(\"\\n\"):\n",
    "                    if line.strip():\n",
    "                        violations.append(line.strip())\n",
    "            \n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": True,\n",
    "                \"valid\": len(violations) == 0,\n",
    "                \"violations\": violations,\n",
    "                \"violations_count\": len(violations),\n",
    "                \"query\": query\n",
    "            }\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            log.error(f\"Failed to validate SPARQL query: {str(e)}\")\n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": False,\n",
    "                \"error\": f\"Failed to validate SPARQL query: {str(e)}\",\n",
    "                \"query\": query\n",
    "            }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def check_query_patterns(query: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Check SPARQL query patterns for common issues and best practices.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Parameters:\n",
    "            query: SPARQL query string\n",
    "            \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            Dictionary with pattern check results\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            # Get the parser tools\n",
    "            parser_tools = sparql_parser_tools()\n",
    "            parse_result = parser_tools[\"parse_sparql_query\"](query)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            if not parse_result.get(\"success\", False):\n",
    "                return parse_result\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Check common patterns and issues\n",
    "            issues = []\n",
    "            warnings = []\n",
    "            suggestions = []\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Extract key components\n",
    "            query_type = parse_result.get(\"query_type\", \"\")\n",
    "            bgps = parse_result.get(\"bgps\", [])\n",
    "            variables = parse_result.get(\"variables\", [])\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Check 1: Unbound variables\n",
    "            var_in_patterns = set()\n",
    "            for triple in bgps:\n",
    "                for position in [\"subject\", \"predicate\", \"object\"]:\n",
    "                    if triple[position].startswith(\"?\"):\n",
    "                        var_in_patterns.add(triple[position])\n",
    "            \n",
    "            for var in variables:\n",
    "                if var not in var_in_patterns:\n",
    "                    issues.append(f\"Unbound variable {var} in SELECT clause\")\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Check 2: Cartesian products (variables only appearing once)\n",
    "            var_counts = {}\n",
    "            for triple in bgps:\n",
    "                for position in [\"subject\", \"predicate\", \"object\"]:\n",
    "                    if triple[position].startswith(\"?\"):\n",
    "                        var_counts[triple[position]] = var_counts.get(triple[position], 0) + 1\n",
    "            \n",
    "            for var, count in var_counts.items():\n",
    "                if count == 1 and var in variables:\n",
    "                    warnings.append(f\"Variable {var} only appears once, may cause a cartesian product\")\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Check 3: Use of rdf:type vs 'a'\n",
    "            type_pattern = re.search(r'\\?\\w+\\s+<http://www\\.w3\\.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type>', query)\n",
    "            if type_pattern:\n",
    "                suggestions.append(\"Consider using 'a' instead of rdf:type for more concise queries\")\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Check 4: Missing prefixes\n",
    "            if query_type and not re.search(r'PREFIX', query, re.IGNORECASE):\n",
    "                suggestions.append(\"Consider adding PREFIX declarations for better readability\")\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Check 5: Missing LIMIT for SELECT queries\n",
    "            if query_type in [\"SelectQuery\", \"Select\"] and not re.search(r'LIMIT', query, re.IGNORECASE):\n",
    "                warnings.append(\"No LIMIT clause found. Consider adding a LIMIT to avoid large result sets\")\n",
    "            \n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": True,\n",
    "                \"issues\": issues,\n",
    "                \"warnings\": warnings,\n",
    "                \"suggestions\": suggestions,\n",
    "                \"issues_count\": len(issues),\n",
    "                \"warnings_count\": len(warnings),\n",
    "                \"has_problems\": len(issues) > 0,\n",
    "                \"query\": query\n",
    "            }\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            log.error(f\"Failed to check SPARQL patterns: {str(e)}\")\n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": False,\n",
    "                \"error\": f\"Failed to check SPARQL patterns: {str(e)}\",\n",
    "                \"query\": query\n",
    "            }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def generate_query_fixes(query: str, validation_result: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Generate suggested fixes for SPARQL query based on validation results.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Parameters:\n",
    "            query: Original SPARQL query string\n",
    "            validation_result: Result from validate_query_against_ontology\n",
    "            \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            Dictionary with suggested fixes\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            # Check if we have validation results\n",
    "            if not validation_result.get(\"success\", False):\n",
    "                return {\n",
    "                    \"success\": False,\n",
    "                    \"error\": \"Invalid validation results\",\n",
    "                    \"query\": query\n",
    "                }\n",
    "                \n",
    "            # If there are no violations, no fixes needed\n",
    "            if validation_result.get(\"valid\", False):\n",
    "                return {\n",
    "                    \"success\": True,\n",
    "                    \"needs_fixes\": False,\n",
    "                    \"suggested_query\": query,\n",
    "                    \"message\": \"No fixes needed, query is valid\"\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Analyze violations\n",
    "            violations = validation_result.get(\"violations\", [])\n",
    "            fix_explanations = []\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Process the original query\n",
    "            # Get the parser tools\n",
    "            parser_tools = sparql_parser_tools()\n",
    "            parse_result = parser_tools[\"parse_sparql_query\"](query)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Initialize variables for tracking fixes\n",
    "            suggested_query = query\n",
    "            fixes_made = False\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Handle domain violations\n",
    "            for violation in violations:\n",
    "                if \"domain\" in violation.lower() and \"subject\" in violation.lower():\n",
    "                    # Extract subject and expected domain from violation message\n",
    "                    subject_match = re.search(r'Subject (\\S+)', violation)\n",
    "                    domain_match = re.search(r'typed as (\\S+)', violation)  \n",
    "                    \n",
    "                    if subject_match and domain_match:\n",
    "                        subject = subject_match.group(1)\n",
    "                        domain = domain_match.group(1)\n",
    "                        \n",
    "                        # Add a type triple for the subject\n",
    "                        if \"?\" in subject:\n",
    "                            # For a variable, add to the WHERE clause\n",
    "                            # Find the WHERE clause\n",
    "                            where_match = re.search(r'WHERE\\s*\\{(.+?)\\}', suggested_query, re.DOTALL)\n",
    "                            if where_match:\n",
    "                                # Insert type statement at beginning of WHERE clause\n",
    "                                where_content = where_match.group(1)\n",
    "                                new_where = f\"WHERE {{\n    {subject} a <{domain}> .\n{where_content}}}\"\n",
    "                                suggested_query = suggested_query.replace(where_match.group(0), new_where)\n",
    "                                fixes_made = True\n",
    "                                fix_explanations.append(f\"Added type assertion for {subject} as {domain}\")\n",
    "                \n",
    "                elif \"not defined\" in violation.lower() and \"property\" in violation.lower():\n",
    "                    # For undefined properties, this is harder to fix automatically\n",
    "                    property_match = re.search(r'Property (\\S+)', violation)\n",
    "                    if property_match:\n",
    "                        property_uri = property_match.group(1)\n",
    "                        fix_explanations.append(f\"Property {property_uri} not found in ontology. Consider using a defined property instead.\")\n",
    "                \n",
    "                elif \"multiple domain\" in violation.lower() or \"multiple range\" in violation.lower():\n",
    "                    # Need to add type constraints\n",
    "                    property_match = re.search(r'Property (\\S+)', violation)\n",
    "                    if property_match:\n",
    "                        property_uri = property_match.group(1)\n",
    "                        if \"multiple domain\" in violation.lower():\n",
    "                            fix_explanations.append(f\"Property {property_uri} has multiple domains. Add a type constraint for the subject.\")\n",
    "                        else:  # multiple range\n",
    "                            fix_explanations.append(f\"Property {property_uri} has multiple ranges. Add a type constraint for the object.\")\n",
    "            \n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": True,\n",
    "                \"needs_fixes\": True,\n",
    "                \"original_query\": query,\n",
    "                \"suggested_query\": suggested_query if fixes_made else None,\n",
    "                \"fixes_made\": fixes_made,\n",
    "                \"fix_explanations\": fix_explanations,\n",
    "                \"violations\": violations,\n",
    "                \"guidance\": \"\\n\".join(fix_explanations) if fix_explanations else \"Manual fixes required. Review the violations and update the query accordingly.\"\n",
    "            }\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            log.error(f\"Failed to generate query fixes: {str(e)}\")\n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": False,\n",
    "                \"error\": f\"Failed to generate query fixes: {str(e)}\",\n",
    "                \"query\": query\n",
    "            }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Add tools to the dictionary\n",
    "    tools[\"validate_query_against_ontology\"] = validate_query_against_ontology\n",
    "    tools[\"check_query_patterns\"] = check_query_patterns\n",
    "    tools[\"generate_query_fixes\"] = generate_query_fixes\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return tools"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 3. SPARQL Execution Tools\n",
    "\n",
    "Now, let's create tools for executing SPARQL queries across both local and remote endpoints."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#| export\n",
    "def sparql_execution_tools() -> Dict[str, Callable]:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Create a set of tools for executing SPARQL queries locally and remotely.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        Dict mapping tool names to tool functions\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    tools = {}\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def execute_local_query(query: str, data_graph: Union[str, Dict]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Execute a SPARQL query against a local RDF graph.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Parameters:\n",
    "            query: SPARQL query string\n",
    "            data_graph: RDF data as JSON-LD or Turtle string\n",
    "            \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            Dictionary with query results\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            # Load the data graph\n",
    "            g = Graph()\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Determine the format\n",
    "            if isinstance(data_graph, dict) or (isinstance(data_graph, str) and data_graph.lstrip().startswith('{')):\n",
    "                # JSON-LD\n",
    "                data_str = json.dumps(data_graph) if isinstance(data_graph, dict) else data_graph\n",
    "                g.parse(data=data_str, format=\"json-ld\")\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                # Assume Turtle\n",
    "                g.parse(data=data_graph, format=\"turtle\")\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Determine query type\n",
    "            query_type = \"UNKNOWN\"\n",
    "            if query.strip().upper().startswith(\"SELECT\"):\n",
    "                query_type = \"SELECT\"\n",
    "            elif query.strip().upper().startswith(\"ASK\"):\n",
    "                query_type = \"ASK\"\n",
    "            elif query.strip().upper().startswith(\"CONSTRUCT\"):\n",
    "                query_type = \"CONSTRUCT\"\n",
    "            elif query.strip().upper().startswith(\"DESCRIBE\"):\n",
    "                query_type = \"DESCRIBE\"\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Execute the query\n",
    "            if query_type == \"SELECT\":\n",
    "                result = g.query(query)\n",
    "                rows = []\n",
    "                for row in result:\n",
    "                    row_dict = {}\n",
    "                    for i, var in enumerate(result.vars):\n",
    "                        value = row[i]\n",
    "                        row_dict[var] = str(value)\n",
    "                    rows.append(row_dict)\n",
    "                \n",
    "                return {\n",
    "                    \"success\": True,\n",
    "                    \"query_type\": query_type,\n",
    "                    \"results\": rows,\n",
    "                    \"count\": len(rows),\n",
    "                    \"variables\": [str(var) for var in result.vars],\n",
    "                    \"query\": query\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            elif query_type == \"ASK\":\n",
    "                result = bool(g.query(query).askAnswer)\n",
    "                return {\n",
    "                    \"success\": True,\n",
    "                    \"query_type\": query_type,\n",
    "                    \"result\": result,\n",
    "                    \"query\": query\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            elif query_type in [\"CONSTRUCT\", \"DESCRIBE\"]:\n",
    "                result_graph = g.query(query).graph\n",
    "                return {\n",
    "                    \"success\": True,\n",
    "                    \"query_type\": query_type,\n",
    "                    \"jsonld\": json.loads(result_graph.serialize(format=\"json-ld\")),\n",
    "                    \"turtle\": result_graph.serialize(format=\"turtle\"),\n",
    "                    \"triples_count\": len(result_graph),\n",
    "                    \"query\": query\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                return {\n",
    "                    \"success\": False,\n",
    "                    \"error\": f\"Unsupported query type: {query_type}\",\n",
    "                    \"query\": query\n",
    "                }\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            log.error(f\"Failed to execute local SPARQL query: {str(e)}\")\n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": False,\n",
    "                \"error\": f\"Failed to execute local SPARQL query: {str(e)}\",\n",
    "                \"query\": query\n",
    "            }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def execute_remote_query(query: str, endpoint_url: str, \n",
    "                          timeout: int = 30,\n",
    "                          format: str = \"json\") -> Dict[str, Any]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Execute a SPARQL query against a remote endpoint using SPARQLWrapper.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Parameters:\n",
    "            query: SPARQL query string\n",
    "            endpoint_url: URL of the SPARQL endpoint\n",
    "            timeout: Query timeout in seconds\n",
    "            format: Result format (json, xml, turtle, csv, etc.)\n",
    "            \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            Dictionary with query results\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            from SPARQLWrapper import SPARQLWrapper, JSON, XML, TURTLE, CSV\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Determine query type\n",
    "            query_type = \"UNKNOWN\"\n",
    "            if query.strip().upper().startswith(\"SELECT\"):\n",
    "                query_type = \"SELECT\"\n",
    "            elif query.strip().upper().startswith(\"ASK\"):\n",
    "                query_type = \"ASK\"\n",
    "            elif query.strip().upper().startswith(\"CONSTRUCT\"):\n",
    "                query_type = \"CONSTRUCT\"\n",
    "            elif query.strip().upper().startswith(\"DESCRIBE\"):\n",
    "                query_type = \"DESCRIBE\"\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Set up the wrapper\n",
    "            sparql = SPARQLWrapper(endpoint_url)\n",
    "            sparql.setQuery(query)\n",
    "            sparql.setTimeout(timeout)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Set the return format\n",
    "            format = format.lower()\n",
    "            if format == \"json\":\n",
    "                sparql.setReturnFormat(JSON)\n",
    "            elif format == \"xml\":\n",
    "                sparql.setReturnFormat(XML)\n",
    "            elif format == \"turtle\":\n",
    "                sparql.setReturnFormat(TURTLE)\n",
    "            elif format == \"csv\":\n",
    "                sparql.setReturnFormat(CSV)\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                sparql.setReturnFormat(JSON)  # Default to JSON\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Execute the query\n",
    "            response = sparql.query()\n",
    "            result = response.convert()\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Process the results based on query type and format\n",
    "            if query_type in [\"SELECT\", \"ASK\"] and format == \"json\":\n",
    "                # Standard SPARQL JSON results\n",
    "                return {\n",
    "                    \"success\": True,\n",
    "                    \"query_type\": query_type,\n",
    "                    \"endpoint\": endpoint_url,\n",
    "                    \"results\": result,\n",
    "                    \"query\": query\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            elif query_type in [\"CONSTRUCT\", \"DESCRIBE\"] and format == \"json\":\n",
    "                # Convert to more readable format\n",
    "                return {\n",
    "                    \"success\": True,\n",
    "                    \"query_type\": query_type,\n",
    "                    \"endpoint\": endpoint_url,\n",
    "                    \"triples\": result,\n",
    "                    \"query\": query\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                # Just return the raw result\n",
    "                return {\n",
    "                    \"success\": True,\n",
    "                    \"query_type\": query_type,\n",
    "                    \"endpoint\": endpoint_url,\n",
    "                    \"format\": format,\n",
    "                    \"raw_result\": str(result),\n",
    "                    \"query\": query\n",
    "                }\n",
    "        except ImportError:\n",
    "            log.error(\"SPARQLWrapper not installed. Install with: pip install sparqlwrapper\")\n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": False,\n",
    "                \"error\": \"SPARQLWrapper not installed. Install with: pip install sparqlwrapper\",\n",
    "                \"query\": query\n",
    "            }\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            log.error(f\"Failed to execute remote SPARQL query: {str(e)}\")\n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": False,\n",
    "                \"error\": f\"Failed to execute remote SPARQL query: {str(e)}\",\n",
    "                \"query\": query,\n",
    "                \"endpoint\": endpoint_url\n",
    "            }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def query_wikidata(query: str, limit: int = 100, timeout: int = 30) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Execute a SPARQL query against the Wikidata endpoint.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Parameters:\n",
    "            query: SPARQL query string\n",
    "            limit: Maximum number of results to return\n",
    "            timeout: Query timeout in seconds\n",
    "            \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            Dictionary with query results\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        # Check and add LIMIT clause if missing\n",
    "        if limit and \"LIMIT\" not in query.upper():\n",
    "            query = query.rstrip() + f\"\\nLIMIT {limit}\"\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Call the execute_remote_query function with Wikidata endpoint\n",
    "        result = execute_remote_query(\n",
    "            query=query,\n",
    "            endpoint_url=\"https://query.wikidata.org/sparql\",\n",
    "            timeout=timeout,\n",
    "            format=\"json\"\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Add Wikidata-specific information\n",
    "        if result.get(\"success\", False):\n",
    "            result[\"source\"] = \"Wikidata\"\n",
    "            result[\"endpoint\"] = \"https://query.wikidata.org/sparql\"\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return result\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def query_dbpedia(query: str, limit: int = 100, timeout: int = 30) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Execute a SPARQL query against the DBpedia endpoint.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Parameters:\n",
    "            query: SPARQL query string\n",
    "            limit: Maximum number of results to return\n",
    "            timeout: Query timeout in seconds\n",
    "            \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            Dictionary with query results\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        # Check and add LIMIT clause if missing\n",
    "        if limit and \"LIMIT\" not in query.upper():\n",
    "            query = query.rstrip() + f\"\\nLIMIT {limit}\"\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Call the execute_remote_query function with DBpedia endpoint\n",
    "        result = execute_remote_query(\n",
    "            query=query,\n",
    "            endpoint_url=\"https://dbpedia.org/sparql\",\n",
    "            timeout=timeout,\n",
    "            format=\"json\"\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Add DBpedia-specific information\n",
    "        if result.get(\"success\", False):\n",
    "            result[\"source\"] = \"DBpedia\"\n",
    "            result[\"endpoint\"] = \"https://dbpedia.org/sparql\"\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return result\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Add tools to the dictionary\n",
    "    tools[\"execute_local_query\"] = execute_local_query\n",
    "    tools[\"execute_remote_query\"] = execute_remote_query\n",
    "    tools[\"query_wikidata\"] = query_wikidata\n",
    "    tools[\"query_dbpedia\"] = query_dbpedia\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return tools"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 4. SPARQL Agent Interface\n",
    "\n",
    "Finally, let's create an Agent interface that brings all these tools together."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#| export\n",
    "class SPARQLToolAgent(Agent):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Agent with specialized tools for working with SPARQL queries.\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(self, name: str = \"sparql-agent\"):\n",
    "        super().__init__(name=name)\n",
    "        self._register_sparql_tools()\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def _register_sparql_tools(self):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Register all SPARQL-specific tools.\"\"\"\n",
    "        # Register parser tools\n",
    "        for name, func in sparql_parser_tools().items():\n",
    "            self.register_tool(func=func, name=name)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Register validator tools\n",
    "        for name, func in sparql_validator_tools().items():\n",
    "            self.register_tool(func=func, name=name)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Register execution tools\n",
    "        for name, func in sparql_execution_tools().items():\n",
    "            self.register_tool(func=func, name=name)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def refine_query_with_ontology(self, query: str, ontology_ttl: str, max_attempts: int = 3) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Refine a SPARQL query against an ontology with iterative improvements.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Parameters:\n",
    "            query: Initial SPARQL query string\n",
    "            ontology_ttl: Turtle representation of the ontology\n",
    "            max_attempts: Maximum number of refinement attempts\n",
    "            \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            Dictionary with the final query and validation results\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        current_query = query\n",
    "        refinement_history = []\n",
    "        \n",
    "        for attempt in range(max_attempts):\n",
    "            # Validate the current query\n",
    "            validation = self.run_tool(\"validate_query_against_ontology\", \n",
    "                                      query=current_query, \n",
    "                                      ontology_ttl=ontology_ttl)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # If valid, we're done\n",
    "            if validation.get(\"valid\", False):\n",
    "                return {\n",
    "                    \"success\": True,\n",
    "                    \"valid\": True,\n",
    "                    \"original_query\": query,\n",
    "                    \"final_query\": current_query,\n",
    "                    \"iterations\": attempt,\n",
    "                    \"refinement_history\": refinement_history,\n",
    "                    \"validation\": validation\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Generate fixes\n",
    "            fixes = self.run_tool(\"generate_query_fixes\", \n",
    "                                query=current_query, \n",
    "                                validation_result=validation)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Record this iteration\n",
    "            refinement_history.append({\n",
    "                \"attempt\": attempt + 1,\n",
    "                \"query\": current_query,\n",
    "                \"validation\": validation.get(\"violations\", []),\n",
    "                \"fixes\": fixes.get(\"fix_explanations\", [])\n",
    "            })\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # If we have a suggested query, use it\n",
    "            if fixes.get(\"fixes_made\", False) and fixes.get(\"suggested_query\"):\n",
    "                current_query = fixes[\"suggested_query\"]\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                # No automatic fixes available, would need LLM intervention here\n",
    "                break\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Return the best query we have so far\n",
    "        return {\n",
    "            \"success\": True,\n",
    "            \"valid\": False,\n",
    "            \"original_query\": query,\n",
    "            \"final_query\": current_query,\n",
    "            \"iterations\": len(refinement_history),\n",
    "            \"refinement_history\": refinement_history,\n",
    "            \"validation\": validation,\n",
    "            \"remaining_issues\": validation.get(\"violations\", []),\n",
    "            \"guidance\": \"Further refinement needed. Consider using an LLM to address remaining issues.\"\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def end_to_end_query(self, query: str, endpoint_url: str = None, \n",
    "                       data_graph: Union[str, Dict] = None,\n",
    "                       ontology_ttl: str = None,\n",
    "                       validate_first: bool = True,\n",
    "                       auto_refine: bool = True,\n",
    "                       timeout: int = 30) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Run a complete end-to-end query process including validation, refinement, and execution.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Parameters:\n",
    "            query: SPARQL query string\n",
    "            endpoint_url: URL for remote endpoint (if None, uses local execution)\n",
    "            data_graph: Local data graph (required for local execution)\n",
    "            ontology_ttl: Optional ontology for validation\n",
    "            validate_first: Whether to validate the query before execution\n",
    "            auto_refine: Whether to automatically refine the query if validation fails\n",
    "            timeout: Query timeout in seconds\n",
    "            \n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            Dictionary with the complete query execution results\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        result = {\n",
    "            \"original_query\": query,\n",
    "            \"workflow\": []\n",
    "        }\n",
    "        \n",
    "        execution_query = query\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Step 1: Validation\n",
    "        if validate_first and ontology_ttl:\n",
    "            validation = self.run_tool(\"validate_query_against_ontology\", \n",
    "                                      query=query, \n",
    "                                      ontology_ttl=ontology_ttl)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            result[\"workflow\"].append({\n",
    "                \"step\": \"validation\",\n",
    "                \"valid\": validation.get(\"valid\", False),\n",
    "                \"issues\": validation.get(\"violations\", [])\n",
    "            })\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Step 2: Refinement (if needed)\n",
    "            if not validation.get(\"valid\", False) and auto_refine:\n",
    "                refinement = self.refine_query_with_ontology(\n",
    "                    query=query,\n",
    "                    ontology_ttl=ontology_ttl\n",
    "                )\n",
    "                \n",
    "                result[\"workflow\"].append({\n",
    "                    \"step\": \"refinement\",\n",
    "                    \"success\": refinement.get(\"success\", False),\n",
    "                    \"iterations\": refinement.get(\"iterations\", 0),\n",
    "                    \"refined_query\": refinement.get(\"final_query\")\n",
    "                })\n",
    "                \n",
    "                # Use the refined query for execution\n",
    "                if refinement.get(\"success\", False):\n",
    "                    execution_query = refinement.get(\"final_query\", query)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Step 3: Execution\n",
    "        if endpoint_url:\n",
    "            # Remote execution\n",
    "            execution = self.run_tool(\"execute_remote_query\",\n",
    "                                    query=execution_query,\n",
    "                                    endpoint_url=endpoint_url,\n",
    "                                    timeout=timeout)\n",
    "        elif data_graph:\n",
    "            # Local execution\n",
    "            execution = self.run_tool(\"execute_local_query\",\n",
    "                                    query=execution_query,\n",
    "                                    data_graph=data_graph)\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            return {\n",
    "                \"success\": False,\n",
    "                \"error\": \"Either endpoint_url or data_graph must be provided for query execution\",\n",
    "                \"original_query\": query,\n",
    "                \"workflow\": result[\"workflow\"]\n",
    "            }\n",
    "        \n",
    "        result[\"workflow\"].append({\n",
    "            \"step\": \"execution\",\n",
    "            \"success\": execution.get(\"success\", False),\n",
    "            \"query_type\": execution.get(\"query_type\", \"UNKNOWN\")\n",
    "        })\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Add the execution results\n",
    "        result[\"execution\"] = execution\n",
    "        result[\"success\"] = execution.get(\"success\", False)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Add any result summary\n",
    "        if execution.get(\"success\", False):\n",
    "            if \"results\" in execution and isinstance(execution[\"results\"], list):\n",
    "                result[\"result_count\"] = len(execution[\"results\"])\n",
    "            elif \"triples_count\" in execution:\n",
    "                result[\"triples_count\"] = execution[\"triples_count\"]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return result"
   ]
  },
