   "source": [
    "# Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook, we've built a comprehensive toolkit for working with SPARQL queries in agentic systems. Our implementation provides:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Robust query parsing** using RDFLib instead of brittle regex approaches\n",
    "2. **Ontology-based validation** with detailed feedback on domain and range violations\n",
    "3. **Automatic query refinement** to fix common issues and inconsistencies\n",
    "4. **Flexible execution options** for both local and remote SPARQL endpoints\n",
    "\n",
    "The `SPARQLToolAgent` class integrates all these capabilities into a coherent workflow, making it easy for agentic systems to construct, validate, and execute SPARQL queries with ontological guidance. This meets the requirements for a more robust approach to OBQC and enables agents to interact with semantic knowledge bases effectively.\n",
    "\n",
    "In future work, we could enhance this toolkit with:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. More sophisticated query generation from natural language using LLMs\n",
    "2. Better integration with the vocabulary tools we explored earlier\n",
    "3. Enhanced explanation and visualization of query results\n",
    "4. Federation across multiple SPARQL endpoints\n",
    "\n",
    "This implementation aligns with CogitareLink's micro-kernel architecture and makes semantic querying accessible to agentic systems."
